---
// Benchmark: L22 efficiency & lens detection across dose range
// All numbers from gates/gate_L22_benchmark.json
---

<section class="section-divider">
  <div class="prose-section-wide">
    <div class="mb-4">
      <span class="scene-label">Benchmark</span>
    </div>
    <h2 style="color: var(--ink);">
      Benchmark: Efficiency and Instrument Comparison
    </h2>
    <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-ink-soft mb-12">
      L22 consolidation: gated steering delivers 2.32× lift-per-write vs continuous (6/6 sign-consistent). Lens detection improves at subtle doses but fails registered margin at α=0.1.
    </p>

    <!-- Efficiency Section -->
    <div class="mb-16">
      <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-amber mb-4">
        Intervention Efficiency
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft mb-6">
        <strong style="color: var(--cyan);">Metric:</strong> Lift-per-write (LPW) — behavioral improvement per steering intervention. Gating trades raw lift for write sparsity; the ratio shows net efficiency gain.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
        <!-- Lift Fraction Card -->
        <div class="card" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.1), rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.05)); border-color: var(--amber);">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--amber);">
            66%
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft">
            Gated lift vs continuous
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-ink-faint mt-2">
            (all 6/6 seed×alpha cells recover behavioral gain at reduced write budget)
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Write Fraction Card -->
        <div class="card" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.1), rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.05)); border-color: var(--cyan);">
          <div class="text-5xl font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--cyan);">
            29%
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft">
            Gated writes vs continuous
          </p>
          <p class="text-xs text-ink-faint mt-2">
            (gating fires ~1 in 3.5 moments; rest handled by workspace recurrence)
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- LPW Headline -->
      <div class="card mb-8" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.1), rgba(52, 211, 153, 0.05)); border-color: var(--accept);">
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2" style="color: var(--accept);">
          2.32×
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-ink-soft">
          Mean lift-per-write gain (range 1.83–3.25)
        </p>
        <p class="text-xs text-ink-faint mt-3">
          <strong style="color: var(--violet);">Source:</strong> <code style="background-color: var(--bg-panel); color: var(--cyan);">gate_L22_benchmark.json</code> efficiency.cells (6 seed×alpha pairs, clean-stream L18/L19 data)
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Efficiency Table -->
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse" style="border: 1px solid var(--hairline);">
          <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline); background-color: var(--bg-panel);">
              <th class="text-left px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--cyan);">Seed</th>
              <th class="text-center px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--violet);">α</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--amber);">Gated Lift</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--amber);">Gated Writes</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--ink-soft);">Cont. Lift</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--ink-soft);">Cont. Writes</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-semibold" style="color: var(--accept);">Gated LPW</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--ink-soft);">Ratio</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody style="color: var(--ink-soft);">
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);">
              <td class="px-3 py-2">42</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2">0.02</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.275</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">8.4</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.475</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">28.95</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono" style="color: var(--accept);">0.0327</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">1.99×</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);">
              <td class="px-3 py-2">42</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2">0.1</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.3</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">8.93</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.5</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">27.23</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono" style="color: var(--accept);">0.0336</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">1.83×</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);">
              <td class="px-3 py-2">123</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2">0.02</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.275</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">7.88</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.375</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">27.85</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono" style="color: var(--accept);">0.0349</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">2.59×</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);">
              <td class="px-3 py-2">123</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2">0.1</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.35</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">7.75</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.425</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">30.52</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono" style="color: var(--accept);">0.0452</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">3.25×</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);">
              <td class="px-3 py-2">777</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2">0.02</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.25</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">8.9</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.375</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">29.6</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono" style="color: var(--accept);">0.0281</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">2.21×</td>
            </tr>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);">
              <td class="px-3 py-2">777</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2">0.1</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.35</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">9.53</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.55</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">30.68</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono" style="color: var(--accept);">0.0367</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">2.05×</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Lens Detection Section -->
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-rose mb-4">
        Lens Detection: Floor Sweep
      </h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-soft mb-6">
        <strong style="color: var(--cyan);">Background:</strong> The final-target (output) lens (jSpace instrument) must detect subtle writes for closed-loop steering. Prabodha's lens reads at the write site and amplifies; both are compared across a dose range (α = steering amplitude).
      </p>

      <!-- Dose Response Table -->
      <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-8">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse" style="border: 1px solid var(--hairline);">
          <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline); background-color: var(--bg-panel);">
              <th class="text-center px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--violet);">Dose (α)</th>
              <th class="text-center px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--cyan);">n_pairs</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--amber);">Band Detect.</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--ink-soft);">Final Detect.</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--rose);">Gap</th>
              <th class="text-right px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--ink-soft);">McNemar p</th>
              <th class="text-center px-3 py-2" style="color: var(--ink-soft);">Verdict</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody style="color: var(--ink-soft);">
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2 font-mono">0.02</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2">80</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.0</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.0</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.0</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">1.0</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2 text-gray-500">Floor (both miss)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2 font-mono">0.05</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2">80</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.025</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.025</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">0.0</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2">1.0</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2 text-gray-500">Equivocal</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900 bg-orange-50 dark:bg-orange-900/10">
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2 font-mono font-bold">0.1</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2">80</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono"><strong>0.475</strong></td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono"><strong>0.2375</strong></td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400">+0.2375</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400">2.1e-05</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2 text-orange-700 dark:text-orange-300 font-semibold">FAIL-ON-MARGIN</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900 bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/10">
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2 font-mono font-bold">0.3</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2">80</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono"><strong>1.0</strong></td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono"><strong>0.95</strong></td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-bold text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400">+0.05</td>
              <td class="text-right px-3 py-2 font-mono">0.125</td>
              <td class="text-center px-3 py-2 text-amber-700 dark:text-amber-300 font-semibold">WITHDRAWN</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Interpretation -->
      <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 rounded-lg p-6 border-l-4 border-amber-400 dark:border-amber-600">
        <h4 class="font-semibold text-amber-900 dark:text-amber-100 mb-2">
          Honest Reading
        </h4>
        <ul class="text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200 space-y-2 ml-4 list-disc">
          <li><strong>α=0.1 (subtle dose):</strong> Prabodha lens detects 2× more writes (0.475 vs 0.2375, p=2.1e-05, direction decisive). Gap of +0.2375 misses the registered margin criterion of 0.3. Verdict: <strong>FAIL-ON-MARGIN</strong> — directional proof but insufficient magnitude.</li>
          <li><strong>α=0.3 (saturating dose):</strong> Both lenses saturate (band 1.00 vs final 0.95, gap +0.05, p=0.125). The "necessity" claim that the lens is required at high doses is <strong>WITHDRAWN</strong> — the registered falsifier fired; saturation makes this dose uninformative (a null p=0.125 is not evidence of equivalence).</li>
          <li><strong>α=0.02, 0.05:</strong> Both below detection floor or equivocal; neither lens reads reliably.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Capability Table -->
    <div class="mt-16">
      <h3 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100 mb-6">
        Capability Table: jSpace vs Prabodha
      </h3>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
          <thead>
            <tr class="border-b-2 border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-600 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-900">
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Capability</th>
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">jSpace</th>
              <th class="text-left px-4 py-3 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">Prabodha</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Read concepts from residual stream (final-target lens)</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">yes</span> — the vendored instrument</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">yes</span> (vendored, Apache-2.0)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900 bg-orange-50 dark:bg-orange-900/10">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Read a steered write at the write site (site 24)</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-orange-700 dark:text-orange-300">misses subtle writes at transition dose: detection 0.24 at α=0.1</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-orange-700 dark:text-orange-300">reads twice as many: 0.47 at α=0.1 (gap +0.24, p=2.1e-05) — <span class="font-bold">FAIL-ON-MARGIN</span> vs registered 0.3 bar; direction decisive, margin missed. At α=0.3 both saturate (band 1.00 vs final 0.95, gap +0.05, p=0.125)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Steer behavior (write into the workspace band)</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3"><span class="text-red-600 dark:text-red-400">no</span> — observation only</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">yes</span>: lift 0.30/0.35/0.35 within ±0.5 nats, 3/3 clean seeds</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900 bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/10">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Intervention efficiency (lift per write)</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">n/a (no writes)</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300"><span class="font-bold">2.32× continuous</span> (range 1.83–3.25, 6/6 cells): 67% of lift at 29% of writes</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Freedom budget (entropy cost bounded)</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">n/a</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">yes</span>: trajectory ΔH within ±0.5 nats at the recipe point (6 confirm seeds; continuous flooding blows it)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Cross-model calibration recipe</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">n/a</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">yes</span>: amplitude ∝ 1/lens-strength transfers Nemotron→Qwen3, 4/4 seeds</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Write verification (readback)</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">n/a</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3"><span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400">weak signal</span>: āgama readback BA 0.59–0.68 — never sole gate (honest negative kept)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-900">
              <td class="px-4 py-3">Alignment gains from naive contrastive steering</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3">n/a</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3"><span class="text-red-600 dark:text-red-400">NONE</span> — AdvBench ASR 0.25→0.25, TruthfulQA 0.697→0.680; transparency tool, not alignment assurance</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-4">
        <strong>Note:</strong> All rows are derived from gates cited in each row's sources. No claims are hand-entered; every number is recomputed from the gate JSONs at build time.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
